textBeforeTable: Please contact us with any additions or corrections. e-mail: usmm.org at comcast.net There are many inconsistencies in spelling, home towns, etc. among our sources. We include other spellings in brackets. A.B.=Able-Bodied Seaman O.S.=Ordinary Seaman F/W=Fireman/Watertender Bosun=Boatswain NatCem - American Battle Monuments Commission National Cemetery Home - home address of designated next of kin, not necessarily the person's home town. BWI=British West Indies PI=Philippine Islands PR=Puerto Rico VI=Virgin Islands NWI=Netherlands West Indies Merchant Mariners killed on U.S. operated ships during World War II Last name begins with "P" and "Q"
